# Cursor rules for Stagiaire

This file mirrors `CLAUDE.md`. Read both `PLAN.md` and `CLAUDE.md` for full context — they are the source of truth.

## Quick reference

**Project status:** planning. No code scaffolded yet.

**Stack (locked):** Next.js 15 (App Router, RSC, Server Actions) · TypeScript strict · Tailwind v4 + shadcn/ui · Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage + Realtime) · Drizzle ORM · react-globe.gl · Resend · Stripe Identity · PostHog · Sentry · Vercel.

## Code style

- Server Components by default; `"use client"` only when interactivity is required
- Server Actions for mutations; avoid API routes unless required by webhooks
- Zod for all validation; share schemas across client/server
- Drizzle queries co-located with the feature
- `cn()` for conditional Tailwind classes; no inline styles
- TypeScript: no `any`, no `as` casts unless unavoidable, narrow types properly
- Components: PascalCase, files: kebab-case
- Early returns; minimal nesting

## File layout

```
app/(public)/    public routes
app/(auth)/      login, signup
app/app/         stagiaire dashboard
app/restaurant/  restaurant dashboard
app/admin/       admin
components/ui/   shadcn primitives
components/features/
db/schema.ts     drizzle schema
db/migrations/
lib/             auth, supabase client, email helpers
data/            seed data
docs/            ADRs / decision logs
```

## Hard rules

- No top-level deps without asking
- No model changes without updating `PLAN.md` §14
- No monetization, payments, housing — out of scope for v1
- Only Michelin-starred restaurants in the directory
- Never fabricate chef names or team data

## Commits

`feat: …` / `fix: …` / `chore: …` / `refactor: …` / `docs: …` — imperative, lowercase, no period.

## Build order

See `PLAN.md` §20. Don't skip ahead.
